                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1823: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-15T09:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 15, 1935—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 15—6:07 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>713. According to a communiqué published this morning the Ethiopian Chargé
                    d’Affaires has informed the Italian Foreign Office that he has received
                    instructions from his Government to return to Addis Ababa and that he would
                    communicate as soon as possible the date and itinerary of his departure. It is
                    also stated that the Foreign Office informed him that he was at liberty to
                    choose both date and itinerary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
